# Project Overview

Multi-tenant SaaS platform (CRM, billing, AI assistants, real-time comms) built with:
- **Next.js 16** (App Router) / **React 19** / **TypeScript 5.9**
- **Supabase** (PostgreSQL 17, RLS for tenant isolation)
- **Telnyx** (voice, messaging, AI assistants)
- **Stripe** (billing/subscriptions)
- **Tailwind CSS v4** (theme via `@theme` in globals.css)
- **Turbo** monorepo with **pnpm** workspaces

## Monorepo Structure

```
apps/tenant/         → Main tenant dashboard (port 3010)
apps/portal/         → Customer support portal
apps/admin/          → System admin app
packages/@tinadmin/core/        → Core SaaS modules
packages/@tinadmin/ui-admin/    → Admin UI components
packages/@tinadmin/ui-consumer/ → Consumer UI components
packages/@tinadmin/telnyx-ai-platform/ → Telnyx AI integration
packages/@tinadmin/config/      → Shared config
packages/integrations/crm/      → CRM provider interfaces
packages/integrations/calendar/  → Calendar provider interfaces
supabase/            → Database migrations
```

## Import Conventions

```typescript
// Core modules (domain-based)
import { signIn } from '@/core/auth';
import { getCurrentTenant } from '@/core/multi-tenancy/server';
import { createClient } from '@/core/database/server';
import { createAdminClient } from '@/core/database/admin-client';

// Type imports — always use `import type`
import type { Database } from '@/core/database';

// Never import internal files directly; use domain index files
```

## Key Patterns

- **Server actions**: `"use server"` directive, in `app/actions/{domain}/`
- **API routes**: `app/api/` following App Router conventions
- **Multi-tenancy**: all tables have `tenant_id`, RLS enforced
- **Provider pattern**: factory pattern for CRM, email, calendar integrations
- **Naming**: PascalCase components, kebab-case routes/actions
